@startuml abstract-engine-relationships

' ============================================================================
' abstract engine architecture - relationship overview
' ============================================================================
' this diagram provides a high-level overview of the abstract engine
' architecture, focusing on structural relationships without implementation
' details. use this for quick comprehension and presentations.
' ============================================================================

' styling and colour scheme
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam classBackgroundColor<<interface>> #E3F2FD
skinparam classBackgroundColor<<abstract>> #FFF9C4
skinparam classBackgroundColor<<manager>> #FFE0B2
skinparam classBackgroundColor<<concrete>> #E8F5E9
skinparam classBackgroundColor<<enum>> #F5F5F5
skinparam classBorderColor #424242
skinparam packageBorderColor #1976D2
skinparam arrowColor #424242
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam nodesep 60
skinparam ranksep 80

' ============================================================================
' engine core - manager hierarchy
' ============================================================================
package "engine" <<Rectangle>> {
  interface IManager <<interface>>
  interface IUpdatable <<interface>>
  abstract Manager <<abstract>>
  abstract UpdatableManager <<abstract>>
  class Engine <<concrete>>
  class Settings <<concrete>>
}

' ============================================================================
' entity system - entity management
' ============================================================================
package "entity" <<Rectangle>> {
  abstract Entity <<abstract>>
  interface EntityFactory <<interface>>
  interface IEntityRepository <<interface>>
  interface IEntityMutator <<interface>>
  class EntityManager <<manager>>
}

' ============================================================================
' transform system - spatial abstraction
' ============================================================================
package "transform" <<Rectangle>> {
  interface ITransform <<interface>>
  interface ITransformable <<interface>>
}

' ============================================================================
' render system - rendering pipeline
' ============================================================================
package "render" <<Rectangle>> {
  interface IRenderable <<interface>>
  interface IRenderItem <<interface>>
  interface IRenderQueue <<interface>>
  class RenderQueue <<concrete>>
  class RenderManager <<manager>>
}

' ============================================================================
' movement system - physics and movement
' ============================================================================
package "movement" <<Rectangle>> {
  interface IMovable <<interface>>
  class MovementManager <<manager>>
}

' ============================================================================
' collision system - collision detection
' ============================================================================
package "collision" <<Rectangle>> {
  interface ICollidable <<interface>>
  class CollisionDetector <<concrete>>
  class CollisionManager <<manager>>
}

' ============================================================================
' input system - input handling
' ============================================================================
package "input" <<Rectangle>> {
  class ActionId <<concrete>>
  enum InputState <<enum>>
  abstract InputEvent <<abstract>>
  interface IInputQuery <<interface>>
  class InputMapping <<concrete>>
  class InputOutputManager <<manager>>
}

' ============================================================================
' scene system - scene management
' ============================================================================
package "scene" <<Rectangle>> {
  interface SceneContext <<interface>>
  abstract Scene <<abstract>>
  class SceneManager <<manager>>
}

' ============================================================================
' relationships: manager hierarchy
' ============================================================================
Manager ..|> IManager
UpdatableManager --|> Manager
UpdatableManager ..|> IUpdatable

' ============================================================================
' relationships: engine orchestration
' ============================================================================
Engine *-- IManager
Engine *-- IUpdatable
Engine o-- RenderManager

' ============================================================================
' relationships: entity system
' ============================================================================
EntityManager --|> Manager
EntityManager ..|> IEntityRepository
EntityManager ..|> IEntityMutator
EntityManager *-- Entity
EntityManager ..> EntityFactory

' ============================================================================
' relationships: transform system
' ============================================================================
ITransformable ..> ITransform : returns

' ============================================================================
' relationships: render system
' ============================================================================
IRenderItem --|> IRenderable
IRenderItem --|> ITransformable
RenderQueue ..|> IRenderQueue
RenderManager --|> Manager
RenderManager *-- RenderQueue
RenderManager ..> IRenderItem

' ============================================================================
' relationships: movement system
' ============================================================================
MovementManager --|> UpdatableManager
MovementManager o-- IMovable
MovementManager ..> ITransformable

' ============================================================================
' relationships: collision system
' ============================================================================
CollisionManager --|> UpdatableManager
CollisionManager *-- CollisionDetector
CollisionManager o-- ICollidable

' ============================================================================
' relationships: input system
' ============================================================================
InputOutputManager --|> UpdatableManager
InputOutputManager ..|> IInputQuery
InputOutputManager *-- InputMapping
InputOutputManager ..> ActionId
InputOutputManager ..> InputState
InputMapping ..> ActionId
InputEvent ..> ActionId

' ============================================================================
' relationships: scene system
' ============================================================================
SceneManager --|> UpdatableManager
SceneManager o-- Scene
SceneManager *-- SceneContext
SceneManager ..> IEntityRepository
SceneManager ..> IRenderQueue
SceneManager ..> IInputQuery
Scene ..> SceneContext
SceneContext ..> IEntityRepository
SceneContext ..> IRenderQueue
SceneContext ..> IInputQuery
SceneContext ..> SceneManager

' ============================================================================
' layout hints for clean visualisation
' ============================================================================
Engine -[hidden]down- EntityManager
EntityManager -[hidden]down- RenderManager
RenderManager -[hidden]down- MovementManager
MovementManager -[hidden]down- CollisionManager
CollisionManager -[hidden]down- InputOutputManager
InputOutputManager -[hidden]down- SceneManager

' ============================================================================
' architectural patterns overview
' ============================================================================
note as ArchitectureOverview
  **abstract engine - architectural patterns**

  **1. template method pattern**
     Manager → UpdatableManager hierarchy
     - consistent lifecycle (init/shutdown/update)
     - subclasses implement protected hooks
     - final methods ensure correct sequencing

  **2. interface segregation principle**
     IEntityRepository (read) vs IEntityMutator (write)
     - clients depend only on needed operations
     - prevents unintended side effects
     - improves testability

  **3. composition over inheritance**
     IRenderItem = IRenderable + ITransformable
     - flexible behaviour composition
     - multiple capability interfaces
     - entities implement combinations

  **4. strategy pattern**
     EntityFactory functional interface
     - pluggable entity creation
     - lambda-compatible design
     - testable factories

  **5. dependency injection**
     SceneManager constructor injection
     - receives IEntityRepository, IRenderQueue, IInputQuery
     - creates SceneContext from dependencies
     - testable with mocks

  **6. deferred state changes**
     SceneManager.pendingKey pattern
     - prevents mid-update transitions
     - ensures consistent state
     - safe scene switching

  **7. observer pattern**
     ICollidable.onCollision callback
     - entities respond to collisions
     - decoupled collision response
     - flexible behaviour per entity

  **architecture summary**
  - 8 packages, 32 classes/interfaces
  - clean separation of concerns
  - dimension-agnostic (2d/3d support)
  - manager-based lifecycle
  - entity-component style design
end note

@enduml
